er%20passed%20away%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20brother%20and%20I%20realized%20we'd%20need%20to%20help%20our%20dad%20sell%20his%20house%20and%20relocate%20to%20either%20the%20Bay%20Area%20near%20my%20brother%20or%20the%20DC%20area%20near%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%20the%20most%20daunting%20task%20was%20helping%20him%20rehome%20his%20dogs.%20Thanks%20to%20my%20father's%20health%20issues%2C%20he%20simply%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20care%20for%20them%20without%20my%20stepmother's%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20helped%20pack%20up%20my%20dad's%20house%20and%20rehome%20his%20dogs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20it%20went%20on%20the%20market%2C%20my%20dad's%20house%20needed%20a%20lot%20of%20work.%20There%20was%20drywall%20repair%20and%20painting%20to%20do%2C%20as%20well%20as%20major%20landscaping%20in%20the%20yard.%20In%20the%20summer%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20spent%20a%20few%20of%20the%20hottest%20days%20in%20the%20Texas%20heat%20wave%20winnowing%20down%20my%20dad's%20possessions%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-i-moved-without-having-a-car-around-us-tips-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epacking%3C%2Fa%3E%20what%20was%20left%20into%20a%20shipping%20cube%2C%20Jenga-style%2C%20for%20pick%20up%20and%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20endless%20Goodwill%20runs%20and%20had%20to%20hire%20someone%20to%20haul%20what%20remained.%20It%20was%20tough%20to%20say%20what%20was%20more%20difficult%2C%20the%20physical%20or%20emotional%20labor.%20Some%20of%20it%20was%20backbreaking%20work%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20hard%20to%20sift%20through%20his%20things%20and%20recall%20the%20memories%20attached%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20challenge%20presented%20by%20Dad's%20dogs%20was%20less%20sweaty%2C%20it%20was%20equally%20heartbreaking.%20I%20had%20to%20find%20someone%20who%20would%20adopt%20them%2C%20so%20I%20posted%20their%20pictures%20on%20social%20media%20and%20hoped%20for%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20found%20loving%20families%20for%20both%20dogs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20student%20of%20mine%20responded%20to%20my%20post%20and%20said%20she%20might%20be%20able%20to%20take%20Stormy%2C%20Dad's%20Chihuahua-Jack%20Russell%20mix.%20My%20brother%20arranged%20a%20Zoom%20meeting%2C%20and%20the%20potential%20new%20owner%20decided%20that%2C%20if%20we%20could%20transport%20her%20to%20the%20DC%20area%2C%20she'd%20adopt%20her.%20We%20agreed.%20With%20one%20dog%20accounted%20for%2C%20there%20was%20still%20one%20to%20go.%20But%20getting%20the%20second%20pup%20adopted%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20an%20even%20greater%20hurdle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELily%20was%20a%20middle-aged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fdogs-that-are-easy-to-train-2018-12%23australian-cattle-dogs-are-good-looking-and-extremely-intelligent-pups-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecattle%20dog%3C%2Fa%3E%20mix%20who%20preferred%20to%20hide%20from%20almost%20anyone%20who%20wasn't%20my%20dad.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20she%20had%20fleas.%20We%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20she'd%20do%20in%20a%20car%2C%20but%20driving%20with%20us%20from%20Texas%20to%20DC%20was%20our%20only%20option%20for%20transporting%20her.%20We%20took%20her%20to%20Petco%20to%20be%20groomed%2C%20and%20then%2C%20once%20again%2C%20I%20turned%20to%20social%20media.%20I%20posted%20on%20Texas%20groups%2C%20cattle%20dog%20rescue%20groups%2C%20and%20groups%20for%20people%20who%20just%20like%20dogs.%20No%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20local%20shelter%2C%20like%20most%2C%20was%20over%20capacity.%20My%20dad%20started%20worrying%20he'd%20need%20to%20put%20her%20down.%20Then%2C%20the%20night%20before%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20supposed%20to%20head%20north%20to%20relocate%20my%20dad's%20car%20and%20a%20few%20last%20possessions%2C%20we%20had%20a%20glimmer%20of%20hope.%20A%20woman%20from%20my%20running%20group%20had%20recently%20lost%20her%20dog%20and%20said%20she%20might%20be%20interested%20but%20would%20need%20to%20meet%20her%20to%20be%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20enough%20for%20us.%20We%20drove%20with%20Lily%20from%20Texas%20to%20Virginia%2C%20staying%20in%20hotel%20rooms%20with%20us%20and%20taking%20the%20dogs%20for%20pee%20breaks%20in%20the%20side%20lots%20of%20every%20convenience%20store%20along%20the%20way.%20We%20met%20Lily's%20potential%20new%20family%20about%20an%20hour%20after%20pulling%20into%20our%20parking%20spot%20at%20home.%20Afterward%2C%20they%20went%20to%20a%20movie%20to%20think%20it%20over%2C%20then%20returned%20to%20claim%20her%20that%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDespite%20the%20tough%20transition%2C%20everyone%20found%20their%20place%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20was%20incredibly%20hard%20for%20Dad%20to%20let%20his%20girls%20go%2C%20it%20helps%20that%20both%20new%20owners%20send%20pictures%20and%20update%20us%2C%20including%20a%20recent%20holiday%20card%20of%20Stormy%20and%20her%20owner%20in%20matching%20festive%20sweaters.%20After%20about%20three%20months%20of%20searching%20for%20a%20place%20that%20met%20all%20of%20his%20requirements%20for%20accessibility%2C%20budget%2C%20and%20location%2C%20Dad%20is%20now%20settled%20as%20well%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20unceasing%20efforts%20of%20Jorge%2C%20his%20extremely%20patient%20real%20estate%20agent.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftiny-house-parents-backyard-saving-money-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elives%20in%20an%20apartment%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20a%20half-hour%20from%20us%2C%20and%20sometimes%20we%20bring%20our%20dog%20over%20to%20visit%20him%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20difficult%20for%20all%20of%20us%20to%20make%20this%20transition%2C%20to%20start%20this%20next%20chapter%20in%20his%20life%20and%20ours%2C%20but%20we're%20grateful%20to%20have%20made%20it%20through%20together%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20everyone%20has%20found%20their%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaregiving-responsibilities-challenges-heart