0looking%20at%20board%20of%20arrivals%20and%20departures.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657cb9dd0ec98e92f7502727%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAuthor%20not%20pictured.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20went%20to%20Spain%20for%20work%2C%20my%20five-month-old%20and%20I%20joined%20to%20get%20out%20of%20our%20comfort%20zone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETraveling%20with%20a%20baby%20reminded%20me%20of%20solo%20travel%20because%20every%20small%20victory%20felt%20like%20a%20huge%20win.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20an%20adapted%20excerpt%20from%20%26quot%3BA%20Trip%20of%20One's%20Own%26quot%3B%20by%20Kate%20Wills.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20few%20weeks%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-i-wished-i-had-done-during-pregnancy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehaving%20my%20daughter%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Blake%2C%20I%20didn't%20leave%20bed%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20house.%20Our%20four%20walls%20became%20our%20whole%20world.%20Going%20for%20a%20shower%20felt%20as%20ambitious%20and%20wonderful%20as%20trekking%20to%20a%20waterfall.%20Meeting%20a%20friend%20for%20a%20coffee%20at%20a%20cafe%20at%20the%20end%20of%20my%20road%20felt%20like%20a%20physical%20impossibility%20%E2%80%94%20those%20stairs%20with%20this%20pram%3F!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20gradually%20Blake%20and%20I%20started%20walking%2C%20and%20walking%20and%20walking.%20With%20the%20country%20still%20locked%20down%20due%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20there%20was%20nowhere%20else%20to%20go%20anyway.%20As%20a%20travel%20writer%2C%20I%20wondered%20if%20I'd%20ever%20get%20my%20suitcase%20out%20again%2C%20or%20if%20I%20might%20one%20day%20show%20Blake%20my%20dusty%20passport%20as%20if%20it%20was%20an%20antique%20relic%20of%20times%20gone%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20chance%20to%20travel%20again%20felt%20exciting%20and%20overwhelming%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20in%20April%202021%2C%20we%20had%20some%20news.%20Guy%2C%20my%20partner%2C%20had%20an%20upcoming%20work%20project%20shooting%20in%20Spain%2C%20so%20we%20decided%20to%20decamp%20there%20for%20a%20few%20months.%20Blake%20was%20five%20months%20old%20and%20the%20thought%20of%20whisking%20her%20out%20of%20our%20very%20small%20comfort%20zone%20was%20daunting.%20I%20lay%20awake%20at%20night%20making%20list%20upon%20list%2C%20thinking%20through%20all%20the%20things%20that%20could%20go%20wrong.%20I%20had%20to%20remind%20myself%20that%20in%20a%20former%20life%2C%20used%20to%20regularly%20jet%20around%20the%20world%20with%20just%20a%20few%20hours'%20notice%20and%20not%20a%20care%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStepping%20foot%20in%20the%20airport%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20over%20a%20year%2C%20I%20felt%20as%20wide-eyed%20and%20incredulous%20as%20Blake%20was%20at%20all%20the%20shiny%20surfaces%2C%20bright%20lights%20and%20so%20many%20screens.%20How%20did%20we%20do%20this%20again%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20new%20protocols%20aside%2C%20it%20turned%20out%20boarding%20a%20747%20is%20just%20like%20riding%20a%20bike.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftravel-with-kids-major-mistakes-best-tips-2022-4%23skimping-where-it-matters-means-youll-end-up-paying-for-it-later-one-way-or-another-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveling%20with%20a%20baby%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20traveling%20solo%20in%20that%20people%20are%20much%20kinder%20to%20you.%20In%20fact%2C%20it's%20even%20better%20than%20that%20and%20a%20bit%20like%20how%20I%20imagine%20celebrities%20get%20treated.%20Every%20queue%20was%20jumped%2C%20the%20cabin%20crew%20can't%20do%20enough%20for%20you%2C%20and%20everyone%20wants%20to%20chat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETraveling%20with%20my%20daughter%20felt%20like%20a%20dream%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20landed%20in%20Cadiz%2C%20a%20sunny%20little%20city%20right%20on%20the%20tip%20of%20Southern%20Spain%2C%20it%20felt%20dream-like%20and%20surreal%20after%20month%20upon%20month%20in%20London.%20Guy%20was%20driven%20straight%20to%20set%20so%20it%20was%20just%20Blake%20and%20me%2C%20two%20girls%20on%20the%20road!%20Like%20Thelma%20and%20Louise%2C%20but%20if%20one%20of%20them%20kept%20soiling%20herself%20and%20had%20only%20just%20started%20eating%20solids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20saw%20the%20sea%20for%20the%20first%20time%20we%20both%20started%20laughing%20out%20loud.%20I%20felt%20a%20surge%20of%20adrenaline%20and%20a%20tingle%20of%20excitement%20as%20I%20connected%20with%20some%20core%20part%20of%20myself%20again.%20All%20the%20worries%20I%20had%20melted%20away%2C%20left%20back%20at%20home%20with%20our%20wooly%20jumpers.%20I%20felt%20like%20me%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsolo-travel-tips-how-to-stay-positive-feel-less-lonely-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20just%20a%20mother%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20was%20my%20equivalent%20of%20fitting%20back%20into%20your%20pre-maternity%20jeans%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHaving%20a%20baby%20actually%20made%20exploring%20a%20new%20country%20easier%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Guy%20at%20work%20most%20days%2C%20Blake%20and%20I%20went%20exploring.%20I%20discovered%20that%20if%20you're%20new%20in%20town%20and%20don't%20speak%20the%20language%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20a%20phrase%20book%20or%20Google%20Translate%20to%20get%20by.%20You%20just%20need%20a%20baby.%20We%20got%20more%20smiles%2C%20waves%2C%20and%20free%20food%20than%20I've%20ever%20had%20in%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDays%20were%20spent%20navigating%20Blake's%20pram%20along%20windy%20cobbled%20streets%2C%20staring%20at%20grand%20Moorish%20buildings%20and%20sipping%20coffees%20in%20pretty%20squares.%20We%20went%20to%20the%20market%20every%20day%20to%20buy%20lemons%20as%20big%20as%20Blake's%20head.%20We%20had%20lunchtime%20cervezas%20(me)%20and%20siestas%20(both%20of%20us).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20unforgettable%20time.%20And%20not%20just%20because%20Blake%20learned%20to%20crawl%20on%20our%20cool%20Spanish%20tiles.%20Living%20in%20Cadiz%20was%20such%20a%20positive%20experience%20it%20made%20me%20wonder%20why%20people%20don't%20use%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaternity-leave-in-europe-vs-us-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematernity%20and%20paternity%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20travel%20more.%20If%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20spending%20all%20day%20in%20a%20constant%20cycle%20of%20feeding%2C%20wiping%2C%20and%20no%20lie-ins%2C%20you%20might%20as%20well%20do%20it%20somewhere%20with%20a%20better%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESoon%2C%20we%20needed%20another%20holiday%20but%20weren't%20sure%20if%20it%20was%20possible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20got%20back%20to%20London%20we%20swore%20that%20now%20we'd%20earned%20our%20baby%20on-board%20badge%2C%20we'd%20make%20regular%20trips%20away%20as%20a%20family.%20And%20then%20Blake%20started%20nursery%20and%20we%20got%20Covid%2C%20and%20chickenpox%2C%20and%20croup%2C%20and%20what%20felt%20like%20every%20other%20illness%20known%20to%20man%20and%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20case%20of%20foot%20and%20mouth%20disease%20%E2%80%94%20beast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20January%20rolled%20around%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I'd%20been%20sentenced%20to%20wipe%20dried-on%20porridge%20off%20a%20high%20chair%20every%20day%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life.%20We%20needed%20a%20holiday.%20A%20proper%20holiday.%20Staycations%20are%20great%20and%20all%2C%20but%20this%20called%20for%20sunshine%20and%20cocktails%20and%20lying%20by%20a%20swimming%20pool%2C%20stat.%20But%20was%20any%20of%20that%20even%20possible%20with%20a%20toddler%20in%20tow%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20to%20fly%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fvisited-went-to-every-country-in-the-world-favorites-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMauritius%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'd%20visited%20this%20island%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20East%20Africa%20many%20years%20ago%20for%20work%2C%20but%20in%20true%20press%20trip%20style%2C%20I'd%20only%20spent%20a%20few%20days%20there.%20From%20what%20I%20remembered%2C%20it%20ticked%20our%20beaches%20and%20palm%20trees%20boxes.%20But%20it%20also%20had%20a%20really%20interesting%20mix%20of%20cultures%20and%20tasty%20food.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20with%20just%20a%20four-hour%20time%20difference%2C%20it%20seemed%20a%20good%20place%20for%20a%20baby.%20I%20was%20also%20intrigued%20to%20see%20more%20of%20the%20spot%20where%20Jeanne%20Baret%2C%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20sail%20around%20the%20world%2C%20had%20settled%20after%20traveling%20the%20world%20disguised%20as%20a%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20suitcases%20held%20raisins%20and%20rice%20cakes%20when%20they%20used%20to%20hold%20bikinis%20and%20beach%20reads%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESummoning%20the%20courage%20for%20our%20first%20long-haul%20flight%20took%20every%20ounce%20of%20my%20professional%20traveler%20expertise.%20But%20packing%20with%20a%20one-year-old%20felt%20very%20different%20from%20my%20solo%20trips.%20While%20once%20my%20tiny%20carry-on%20would've%20been%20stuffed%20with%20bikinis%20and%20beach%20reads%2C%20now%20I%20had%20three%20suitcases%2C%20one%20containing%20an%20entire%20compartment%20just%20for%20raisins%20and%20rice%20cakes.%20And%20although%20it%20wasn't%20a%20holiday%20as%20I'd%20known%20it%20before%20(I%20have%20never%20been%20less%20tanned%20or%20read%20fewer%20books)%2C%20it%20was%20a%20whole%20new%20kind%20of%20adventure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraveling%20with%20a%20baby%20is%20weirdly%20similar%20to%20solo%20travel%20in%20that%20every%20small%20victory%20feels%20huge.%20It%20has%20that%20same%20intensity%20to%20it%2C%20making%20memories%20emotional%20and%20vivid.%20I%20hope%20I'll%20never%20forget%20dancing%20on%20the%20beach%20with%20Blake%20at%20sunset%20or%20pointing%20out%20fruit%20bats%20to%20her%20like%20they%20were%20ducks%20in%20the%20park.%20Toddlers%20love%20water%20and%20the%20fact%20it%20was%20now%20the%20shallow%20end%20of%20a%20swimming%20pool%20and%20not%20a%20freezing%20cold%20puddle%20in%20the%20park%20upgraded%20my%20quality%20of%20life%20no%20end.%20Blake%20greedily%20drank%20up%20the%20new%20scenery%2C%20and%20said%20%26quot%3Bflower%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20while%20pointing%20at%20a%20lotus%20(Jeanne%20Baret%20would%20be%20proud).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20were%20also%20moments%20that%20were%2C%20for%20want%20of%20a%20better%20word%2C%20a%20total%20shitshow.%20Hand-washing%20poo%20out%20of%20a%20sleeping%20bag%20in%20the%20bathroom%20sink%20in%20our%20Mauritius%20hotel%20room%20probably%20wasn't%20my%20idea%20of%20holiday%20heaven.%20On%20our%20first%20night%20in%20a%20hotel%20in%20Spain%2C%20we%20were%20so%20scared%20of%20waking%20her%20in%20the%20bedroom%20that%20we%20sat%20on%20the%20floor%20in%20the%20bathroom%20and%20ate%20cold%20takeaway%20pizza.%20There%20were%20times%20on%20the%2012-hour%20flight%20when%20it%20seemed%20like%20it%20would%20never%20end.%20But%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20I'm%20pleased%20to%20report%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsurprising-things-about-moving-to-europe-from-us-barcelona-spain%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveling%20with%20a%20small%20child%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20only%20possible%20but%20infinitely%20pleasurable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D3f71c2dee0aa2bccc31f3f1d6ec31bb184779c0b40a87f4690f3b39f9aeb3459%26postID%3D657c9dcd691ac4e99676e85c%26postSlug%3Dsolo-traveler-surprised-how-much-she-like-traveling-with-baby-2023-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FTrip-Ones-Own-Heartbreak-Traveling%252Fdp%252F1728255279%252Fref%253Dasc_df_1728255279%252F%253Ftag%253Dhyprod-20%2526linkCode%253Ddf0%2526hvadid%253D598277352385%2526hvpos%253D%2526hvnetw%253Dg%2526hvrand%253D1189945530152872100%2526hvpone%253D%2526hvptwo%253D%2526hvqmt%