Fi.insider.com%2F656f43fc58e7c0c29a29acd7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20and%20her%20partner%20are%20photographed%20in%20Glasgow%2C%20Scotland.%3Cp%3EMikhaila%20Friel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20partner%20and%20I%20are%20complete%20opposites%3A%20He%20loves%20bars%20and%20pubs%20while%20I%20rarely%20drink.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThankfully%2C%20we're%20both%20open%20to%20trying%20new%20things%2C%20which%20makes%20date%20nights%20fun.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20we%20navigate%20our%20relationship%20as%20opposites.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20partner%2C%20Scott%2C%20and%20I%20differ%20slightly%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20our%20respective%20definitions%20of%20a%20fun%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20homebody%20who%20loves%20curling%20up%20with%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%20and%20a%20good%20book%2C%20and%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsober-curious-why-i-rarely-drink-alcohol-not-tee-total-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erarely%20drink%20alcohol%3C%2Fa%3E%20(I'll%20sometimes%20have%20one%20or%20two%20drinks%20at%20social%20events).%20Meanwhile%2C%20Scott%20is%20extroverted%20and%20enjoys%20spending%20Friday%20nights%20at%20the%20local%20pub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20first%20met%20three%20years%20ago%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhinge-boyfriend-why-dating-is-better-offline-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20our%20date%20nights%20took%20place%20at%20home%20for%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20months%20of%20our%20relationship.%20When%20the%20world%20opened%20up%2C%20we%20realized%20how%20different%20we%20were%20when%20it%20came%20to%20socializing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20going%20to%20lie%20and%20say%20we've%20never%20had%20an%20argument%20over%20our%20differences%20%E2%80%94%20it%20would%20probably%20be%20strange%20if%20we%20hadn't.%20But%20through%20communication%20and%20compromises%2C%20we've%20managed%20to%20not%20let%20it%20affect%20our%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20we%20make%20date%20nights%20work%20as%20opposites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20communicate%20our%20expectations%20ahead%20of%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20and%20I%20have%20been%20on%20some%20fantastic%20dates%20over%20the%20years%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fi-went-to-a-graveyard-for-second-date-was-weird-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexploring%20the%20local%20necropolis%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fclimbing-every-week-even-though-progress-is-slow-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebouldering%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20as%20catching%20comedy%20shows%20in%20our%20home%20city%2C%20Glasgow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBust%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20a%20standard%20date%20night%20involves%20dinner%20and%20drinks%2C%20either%20alone%20or%20with%20other%20couples.%20Before%20meeting%20Scott%2C%20I%20wasn't%20a%20regular%20pub-goer%20but%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20much%20I%20loved%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20city%20is%20known%20for%20its%20buzzy%20nightlife%2C%20but%20you%20can%20also%20find%20pubs%20that%20have%20a%20relaxed%20atmosphere.%20One%20of%20my%20favorite%20pubs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fbabbitybowsterglasgow%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBabbity%20Bowster%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20a%20selection%20of%20board%20games%2C%20including%20chess%20and%20Scrabble%2C%20which%20Scott%20and%20I%20often%20play%20when%20we%20visit.%20He%20usually%20orders%20a%20beer%20for%20himself%2C%20and%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mikhaila%20and%20scott%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62f3d0e25b790400198acff9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMikhaila%20and%20Scott%20at%20a%20pub%20in%20Glasgow.%3Cp%3EMikhaila%20Friel%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20mistake%20we%20initially%20made%20(and%20let's%20be%20honest%2C%20sometimes%20still%20make)%20was%20not%20communicating%20what%20time%20we%20planned%20to%20leave%20an%20event.%20This%20is%20especially%20important%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fpurchased-first-home-uk-economic-crisis-have-no-regrets-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewe%20live%20together%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Scott%20often%20longed%20to%20stay%20out%20until%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20the%20morning%2C%20while%20I%20was%20ready%20to%20go%20to%20sleep%20by%2011%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20we%20try%20our%20best%20to%20compromise%20on%20an%20estimated%20time%20to%20leave%20before%20we%20go%20out.%20This%20might%20sound%20odd%20to%20some%20people%2C%20but%20it%20has%20made%20things%20a%20lot%20easier%20for%20us%20and%20prevented%20potential%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe've%20combined%20both%20of%20our%20worlds%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20great%20thing%20about%20pubs%20in%20Glasgow%20is%20the%20variety%20of%20events%2C%20from%20quiz%20nights%20to%20writing%20workshops%20and%20open%20mic%20competitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20poetry%20and%20live%20music%2C%20and%20I%20recently%20discovered%20an%20open%20mic%20night%20for%20spoken-word%20artists%20at%20a%20pub%20in%20the%20city's%20West%20End.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20has%20gone%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20open%20mic%20nights%20with%20me%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months%20because%20he%20knows%20it's%20important%20to%20me.%20The%20fact%20that%20it's%20in%20a%20pub%20is%20even%20better%2C%20as%20it's%20somewhere%20that%20he%20feels%20comfortable%20despite%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20event%20being%20outside%20of%20something%20he%20would%20typically%20sign%20up%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20together%20for%20three%20years%2C%20I%20love%20that%20Scott%20and%20I%20are%20both%20open%20to%20trying%20new%20experiences%20together.%3C