n%20June.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20allowed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20to%20move%20ahead%20on%20Friday.%20The%20company%20is%20accused%20of%20failing%20to%20pay%20staff%20their%20promised%20annual%20bonuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-employees-sue-unpaid-bonuses-lawsuit-elon-musk-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20in%20June%20by%20Mark%20Schobinger%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company's%20former%20head%20of%20compensation%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20himself%20and%20thousands%20of%20other%20current%20and%20former%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20claimants%20are%20suing%20the%20company%20for%20allegedly%20failing%20to%20honor%20verbal%20promises%20that%20all%20employees%20working%20at%20X%20as%20of%20January%201%2C%202023%2C%20would%20be%20paid%20a%20portion%20of%20their%20annual%20bonuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20amount%20owed%20exceeds%20%245%20million%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitterlayofflawsuit.com%2F_files%2Fugd%2Febbd24_3db80b2cd5fa410782e579698e624e47.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecourt%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%C2%A0the%20plaintiff's%20attorney%2C%20Shannon%20Liss-Riordan%2C%20said%20the%20bonuses%20owed%20amounted%20to%20%26quot%3Btens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20estimate%20about%20a%20couple%20thousand%20employees%20would%20have%20been%20eligible%20for%20the%20bonuses%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Judge%20Vince%20Chhabria%20dismissed%20calls%20from%20X's%20lawyers%20to%20throw%20out%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyers%20had%20argued%20that%20the%20company%20couldn't%20be%20forced%20to%20uphold%20verbal%20contracts%20between%20Schobinger%20and%20the%20former%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20judge%20wrote%20that%20Schobinger's%20case%20%26quot%3Bplausibly%20stated%20a%20breach%20of%20contract%20claim%26quot%3B%20under%20California%20state%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20Schobinger%20did%20what%20Twitter%20asked%2C%20Twitter's%20offer%20to%20pay%20him%20a%20bonus%20in%20return%20became%20a%20binding%20contract%20under%20California%20law.%20And%20by%20allegedly%20refusing%20to%20pay%20Schobinger%20his%20promised%20bonus%2C%20Twitter%20violated%20that%20contract%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20claims%20that%20management%20at%20Twitter%20promised%20employees%20they%20would%20be%20paid%2050%25%20of%20their%202022%20annual%20bonus%20if%20they%20stayed%20with%20the%20company%20during%20Musk's%20takeover%2C%20which%20was%20finalized%20in%20October%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20annual%20bonuses%20are%20usually%20paid%20out%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20the%20following%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fzacharyfolk%2F2023%2F12%2F23%2Felon-musks-x-breached-twitter-worker-contracts-by-refusing-bonuses-judge-rules%2F%3Fsh%3D3c98ee56146d%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTwitter%2520historically%2520paid%2520bonuses%2520in%2520the%2520first%2520quarter%2520of%2520the%2520new%2520year%25E2%2580%2594usually%2520March%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Forbes.%3C%2Fa%3E%20According%20to%20Schobinger%2C%20those%20payments%20never%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX's%20lawyers%20argued%20that%20this%20verbal%20contract%20did%20not%20stand%20up%20under%20Texas%20law%2C%20where%20they%20claimed%20the%20case%20should%20be%20tried.%20But%20the%20judge%20ruled%20that%20the%20case%20would%20be%20governed%20by%20California%20law%2C%20and%2C%20regardless%20of%20state%20law%2C%20all%20claims%20for%20dismissal%20%26quot%3Bfailed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchobinger%20quit%20in%20May%20and%20said%20that%20X%20%26quot%3Breneging%20on%20various%20promises%20it%20had%20made%20to%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20includi