20not%20what%20it%20was%20in%20late%20September.%20It%20has%20changed%20a%20lot.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20former%20leader%20of%20the%20Labour%20Party%2C%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20in%20the%20last%20British%20election%20and%20the%20MP%20of%20Islington%20North%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20been%20more%20right.%20The%20mood%20in%20British%20politics%20has%20indeed%20shifted%20during%20the%20last%20two%20months.%20Both%20the%20ruling%20Conservative%20Party%20or%20the%20Tories%20and%20the%20opposition%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party%2C%20are%20trying%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20shifting%20political%20dynamics%2C%20which%20have%20also%20impacted%20another%20important%20player%2C%20the%20Liberal%20Democrats%20or%20Lib%20Dems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20society%20at%20large%20has%20also%20encountered%20fresh%20questions%20in%20the%20last%20two%20months.%20A%20few%20phrases%20are%20in%20the%20air%3A%20the%20Liberation%20Movement%20of%20Palestine%2C%20Zionism%2C%20anti-Semitism%2C%20the%20far-left%2C%20and%20the%20far-right%2C%20etc.%20And%20the%20Metropolitan%20Police%20of%20London%20has%20also%20been%20compelled%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20changing%20scenario.%20Compared%20to%20the%20pre-October%20days%2C%20the%20surveillance%20on%20public%20meetings%2C%20protest%20marches%2C%20and%20rallies%20have%20tightened%20to%20a%20large%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20such%20changes%20are%20an%20expression%20of%20the%20responses%20of%20British%20society%20and%20politics%20to%20the%20anti-war%20campaign%20Britain%20has%20been%20witnessing%20for%20the%20last%20two%20months.%20Since%20the%20second%20week%20of%20October%2C%20Britain%20has%20virtually%20returned%20to%20the%20days%20of%20the%20movement%20against%20the%20wars%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%20a%20couple%20of%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%20every%20Saturday%2C%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fgallery%2F2023%2F10%2F29%2Fhundreds-of-thousands-march-worldwide-against-israeli-bombardment-of-gaza%5C%22%3Eare%20taking%20to%20the%20streets%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20order%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fpro-palestine-protesters-disrupt-oxford-street-christmas-shoppers-in-call-to-boycott-pro-israel-brands-13036859%5C%22%3Eoppose%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fdec%2F23%2Fprotest-in-oxford-street-london-calls-for-gaza-ceasefire-and-boycott-of-brands%5C%22%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20military%20offensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Gaza.%20People%20are%20also%20holding%20marches%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fworld%2Fthousands-rally-world-support-of-israel-palestine-8983038%2F%5C%22%3Esupport%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20albeit%20of%20a%20much%20smaller%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Corbyn%20has%20become%20the%20face%20of%20pro-Palestine%20protests%2C%20the%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Boris%20Johnson%20could%20be%20seen%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Faustralia-news%2F2023%2Fnov%2F05%2Fboris-johnson-and-scott-morrison-join-forces-on-solidarity-trip-to-israel%5C%22%3Epro-Israel%20marches%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Incidents%20like%20anti-war%20demonstrations%20in%20front%20of%20the%20parliament%2C%20a%20demonstration%20of%20social%20activists%20inside%20the%20parliament%20premises%2C%20protests%20outside%20the%20offices%20of%20the%20Labour%20leader%20Keir%20Starmer%20characterise%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20time.%20In%20short%2C%20the%20current%20Palestine%20crisis%20has%20come%20to%20take%20the%20centrestage%20in%20British%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-israel-palestine-war-is-a-stain-on-every-one-of-us%5C%22%3EThe%20Israel-Palestine%20War%20Is%20a%20Stain%20on%20Every%20One%20of%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20the%20Big%20Brother%20USA%2C%20the%20entire%20British%20%E2%80%98political%20establishment%E2%80%99%20has%20openly%20sided%20with%20Israel.%20While%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20visited%20Israel%20to%20convey%20his%20message%20of%20solidarity%20to%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20the%20current%20Labour%20leader%20(widely%20perceived%20as%20the%20would-be%20prime%20minister)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6275507%2Fkeir-starmer-interview-uk%2F%5C%22%3ESir%20Keir%20Starmer%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20taken%20a%20similar%20stand.%20Things%2C%20however%2C%20started%20changing%20since%20October%2014%2C%20when%20several%20organisations%2C%20including%20Stop%20the%20War%20Coalition%20and%20the%20Palestine%20Solidarity%20Campaign%2C%20convened%20a%20pro-Palestine%20protest%20march%2C%20which%20saw%20the%20gathering%20of%20over%20150%2C000%20people.%20Corbyn%20was%20the%20only%20British%20MP%20to%20attend%20this%20very%20first%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20subsequently%2C%20the%20attendance%20in%20these%20weekly%20protest%20marches%20continued%20to%20surge%2C%20reaching%20over%20800%2C000%20in%20the%20fourth%20march%20since%20October%207.%20This%20is%20being%20accompanied%20by%20the%20growing%20participation%20of%20MPs%2C%20social%20activists%2C%20and%20trade%20union%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20surge%20in%20street%20demonstrations%20has%20already%20exerted%20enough%20pressure%20on%20British%20political%20parties%20of%20every%20stripe%2C%20and%20especially%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party.%20While%20the%20Muslim%20community%20in%20Britain%20has%20traditionally%20been%20a%20Labour%20constituency%2C%20Sir%20Keir%E2%80%99s%20stand%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20favour%20has%20caused%20widespread%20discontent%20among%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20committed%20Muslim%20voters.%20The%20impact%20has%20been%20felt%20within%20the%20party%20as%20well.%20More%20than%20a%20hundred%20Labour%20councillors%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Foct%2F16%2Flabour-councillors-quit-party-in-protest-at-keir-starmers-israel-stance%5C%22%3Ehave%20already%20resigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protest%20against%20Sir%20Keir%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20Israel.%20In%20an%20unprecedented%20move%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-london-67435955%5C%22%3E56%20Labour%20MPs%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20against%20the%20Labour%20leader%E2%80%99s%20stand%20to%20vote%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20the%20parliament.%20Moreover%2C%20at%20least%2010%20members%20of%20his%20shadow%20cabinet%20have%20openly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Foct%2F25%2Flabour-party-divisions-israel-gaza-starmer%5C%22%3Eopposed%20his%20views%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Starmer%20has%20never%20faced%20such%20a%20strong%20opposition%20within%20his%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20Tories%20could%20not%20also%20escape%20the%20heat%20of%20the%20anti-war%20campaign.%20In%20a%20%3Cem%3ETimes%3C%2Fem%3E%20opinion%20piece%2C%20Suella%20Braverman%2C%20the%20former%20Home%20Secretary%20and%20the%20most%20vocal%20Tory%20leader%20against%20the%20pro-Palestine%20protesters%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Fnov%2F08%2Fsuella-braverman-accuses-police-of-double-standards-on-rallies%5C%22%3Eaccused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Metropolitan%20Police%20of%20playing%20%E2%80%9Cfavourites%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20protesters%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20being%20tougher%20on%20right-wing%20extremists.%20She%20even%20requested%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20the%20police%20to%20impose%20a%20ban%20on%20pro-Palestine%20marches.%20The%20Metropolitan%20Police%2C%20however%2C%20didn%E2%80%99t%20oblige%2C%20as%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20grave%20law-and-order%20problem%20by%20banning%20protests%20involving%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20people.%20Following%20this%20development%2C%20Sunak%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Frishi-sunak-suella-braverman-david-cameron%5C%22%3Ereplaced%3C%2Fa%3E%20Braverman%20with%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20David%20Cameron%2C%20who%20is%20known%20as%20a%20centre-right%20politician%20in%20the%20Conservative%20Party.%20The%20ruling%20Conservatives%2C%20thus%2C%20are%20also%20caught%20up%20in%20this%20whirlwind%20caused%20by%20the%202023%20Israel-Hamas%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20these%20two%20larger%20parties%2C%20the%20Liberal%20Democrats%20%E2%80%93%20the%20second%20choice%20of%20the%20British%20Muslims%20after%20the%20Labour%20Party%20%E2%80%93%20have%20also%20been%20affected%20by%20the%20war.%20Due%20to%20the%20pressure%20of%20its%20Muslim%20and%20leftist%20members%2C%20the%20party%20has%20supported%20the%20ceasefire.%20Lib%20Dem%20members%20could%20even%20be%20seen%20in%20anti-war%20marches%20with%20their%20banners.%20The%20wide%20participation%20of%20trade%20unions%2C%20which%20in%20Britain%20include%20workers%20of%20all%20political%20colours%2C%20has%20also%20added%20to%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20anti-war%20campaign.%20Most%20of%20the%20trade%20unions%20including%20the%20RMT%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20trade%20union%20covering%20the%20transport%20sector%20%E2%80%93%20Unite%20the%20Union%2C%20and%20the%20UNISON%20have%20taken%20part%20in%20pro-Palestine%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20last%20two%20months%2C%20Britain%20has%20witnessed%20a%20surge%20in%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20movement%20around%20pro-Palestine%20and%20anti-war%20activism.%20While%20Corbyn%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-politics-65102128%5C%22%3Eexit%20from%20the%20Labour%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%20signalled%20a%20huge%20setback%20for%20the%20British%20Left%2C%20they%20are%20now%20gaining%20fresh%20steam%20due%20to%20these%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fgallery%2F2023%2F10%2F20%2Fphotos-palestine-solidarity-rallies-around-the-world%5C%22%3Eprotest%20marches%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20